<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>GIPHY API</title>
    <meta name="description" content="A cool thing made with Glitch">
    <link id="favicon" rel="icon" href="https://glitch.com/edit/favicon-app.ico" type="image/x-icon">
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <!-- import the webpage's stylesheet -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">

  </head>
  <body style="background-image: url(<%= gif %>)">

    <main>
      <h1>
        Getting Started with the GIPHY&nbsp;API
      </h1>
      
      <section>
        <h2 class="section-header">
          1. Remix this app 🎏
        </h2>
        <div>
          <a href="https://glitch.com/edit/#!/remix/giphy-starter-app">
            <img
                  src="https://cdn.glitch.com/2703baf2-b643-4da7-ab91-7ee2a2d00b5b%2Fremix-button.svg"
                  alt="Remix on Glitch"
              />
          </a>      
        </div>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2 class="section-header">
           2. Create a Developer Account on GIPHY    
        </h2>
        <ol>    
          <li>
            Start by <a href="https://giphy.com/join?next=%2Foauth%2Fauthorize%2F%3Fresponse_type%3Dcode%26client_id%3DC7yftGDVCAhmaTnJCKv3eNaRsANYTDDf7PA9jZbw%26redirect_uri%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fdevelopers.giphy.com%252Foauth%252Fexchange%252F">creating a developer account</a> with GIPHY.
          </li>
          <li>
            Next click the "Create an App" button
          </li>
          <li>
            Give your app a name, and a description. 
          </li>
          <li>
            Click the box labeled "I only want to use the GIPHY API"
          </li>
           <li>
            Create your app!
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2 class="section-header">
           3. Copy the API key     
        </h2>
        <p>
          Now you should see a Dashboard page with your new app.
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Copy the red text labelled: <span class="callout">API Key</span></li>
        </ol>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2 class="section-header">
           4. Update your .env file
        </h2>
        <p>
          Return to your Glitch project. 
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Find a file called <span class="callout">.env</span> in your project.</li>
          <li>Paste the API key on the line with the text: <span class="callout">GIPHY_KEY=</span></li>
        </ol>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2 class="section-header">
           5. Confirm that your .env is set up correctly
        </h2>
      <% if (!success) { %>
        <form method="POST" action="/test" id="test">
          <button type="submit">Did it work?</button>
          <span class="test-alert"><%= text %></span>
        </form>
      <% } %>
       <% if (success) { %>
        <p>🎉🎉🎉 Congrats! It worked! 🎉🎉🎉</p>
      <% } %>

      </section>
       <section>
        <h2 class="section-header">
           6. Build something great!
        </h2>
        <p>Checkout some other Glitch starter apps for inspiration on what to do next!</p>
         <ul>
           <li>Make a Discord bot <a href="https://starter-discord.glitch.me/">Discord Botkit Starter > </a></li>
           <li>Build a YTMND Clone <a href="https://gif-party.glitch.me/">Gif Party ></a></li>
           <li>Make a gif Search engine <a href="https://superhi-jiffy.glitch.me/">Jiffy Gif Search</a></li>
         </ul>
      </section>
    </main>

    <!-- include the Glitch button to show what the webpage is about and
          to make it easier for folks to view source and remix -->
    <div class="glitchButton" style="position:fixed;top:20px;right:20px;"></div>
    <script src="https://button.glitch.me/button.js"></script>

  </body>
</html>
